cskinner@triode.apana.org.au (Christopher T Skinner) writes:

>I hear from Mr Burroughs at NIST that the USA Government has adopted a 
>Digital Signature "FIPS -186"
>What is it? It couldn't be the old "DSS" because that is under a PKP Patent
>cts NSW


FIPS186 is DSS. NIST is of the opinion that DSS does not violate PKP's 
patents. PKP (or at least Jim Bidzos) takes the position that it does. 
But for various reasons, PKP won't sue the government. But Bidzos 
threatens to sue private parties who infringe. Stay tuned....

